Sentencas: The performance and stability of the Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite with a weight ratio of 7:3 (SSC-SDC73) were studied and evaluated as oxygen electrode of high temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells (SOECs).
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The co-synthesized SSC-SDC73 oxygen electrode exhibited better electrochemical activity and stability than that of physically mixed one for the oxygen oxidation reaction.
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The effect of anodic polarization current on the co-synthesized SSC-SDC73 oxygen electrode was further investigated under the relative low and high currents at 800 degrees C in air, respectively.
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The obtained results demonstrated that co-synthesized SSC-SDC73 oxygen electrode exhibited a better stability under low anodic polarization current.
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: While a higher anodic polarization current could promote the slight agglomerate and delamination of the electrode.
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Therefore, the polarization current is a key operating parameter for SSC-SDC73 oxygen electrode under the SOEC operation conditions.
Titulo: Performance and stability of co-synthesized Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite oxygen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells
